    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (79.92) and **James Wood** (73.18) headline our production expectations. **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** benefits significantly from a favorable matchup against Arrighetti, where his dynamic platoon advantage (+7%) and the opponent's slow delivery\u2014which we project will yield a 100% stolen base opportunity rate\u2014create an elite ceiling. Similarly, **James Wood** is locked into the leadoff spot against the leaky 4.76 xERA of Hudson, providing the perfect engine for our stolen base-starved lineup. **Corbin Carroll** (71.54) remains a foundational start as well; despite facing a competent arm in King, his .372 xwOBA and prime hitting position keep him well above the 70-point threshold.\n\nThe tightest margin on our lineup card today involves **Vinnie Pasquantino**, who finished just shy of the 40-point threshold at 39.32. While **Vinnie Pasquantino** usually provides steady value, his severe platoon disadvantage against Detmers (-15%) and the negative impact of facing a sub-3.10 xERA arm pushed him into the bench rotation. Meanwhile, **Jose Caballero** remains in the lineup despite a lower base projection because the specific situational boost from Arrighetti\u2019s slow delivery\u2014which theoretically offsets his bottom-of-the-order placement\u2014keeps his efficiency high enough to chase those precious, scarce stolen bases.\n\nWe are proceeding with caution regarding **Dalton Rushing** (46.97) and **Mickey Moniak** (50.49). **Dalton Rushing** is battling a L/L platoon disadvantage against Imanaga, and while wind blowing out provides a marginal buffer, he remains a volatile start. **Mickey Moniak** faces the most significant structural headwind; despite a positive platoon split, the combination of a pitcher with a 3.04 xERA and stadium-specific wind blowing in (-5%) nearly pushed him into the bench tier. Ensure monitoring for any late-inning defensive substitutions, as these marginal plays represent the most significant risk to our daily efficiency targets.",
